<CENTER>
<H2>
23rd Annual East Coast <BR>
Commercial Fishermen's <BR>
and Aquaculture Trade Exposition
</H2>
<H3>
January 17-19, 1997<BR>
Wicomico County Civic Center<BR>
Salisbury, Maryland
<P>
Don Webster, Eastern Shore Area Agent
</H3>
</CENTER>
Watermen and aquaculturists will be able to learn about new and exciting innovations at the 1997 East Coast Commercial Fishermen's and Aquaculture Trade Exposition. The <A HREF="#COMM">seminars for watermen</A> are included in the price of admission to the trade show. There will be an additional charge of $20 for the <A HREF="#AQUA">aquaculture seminars</A>.
<P>
Seminar programs are produced in cooperation with the Mid-Atlantic Sea Grant Advisory Programs to educate commercial watermen, aquaculturists and other marine interests on topics having an impact on their lives and businesses. Extension programs are available to all persons regardless of race, color, religion, national origin, sex, or handicap. Sea Grant is a program of the National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) and funds research, education, and extension program in all of our nation's coastal and Great Lakes states. These seminar programs are annually planned with advice and assistance from the Maryland Waterman's Association Board of Directors.
<P>
<A NAME="COMM"></A>
