                <TD COLSTART="1" COLSPAN="1" ROWSTART="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="75" VALIGN="TOP">
                </TD>
                <TD COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="1" WIDTH="287">
<font size=4 color="#2222c2">Women's Luncheon: Plant Your Feet Firmly in Mid-Air</font>
<p>
<font size=4 color="#2222c2">V</font>irginia Mason Foundation's Women's Advisory Council is presenting its second annual educational luncheon forum at The Westin Hotel in Seattle on Tuesday, Nov. 12, featuring provocative author and lecturer, Janet Lapp, Ph.D.
<p>
<font size=4 color="#2222c2">D</font>r. Lapp is the author of <i>Dancing With Tigers</i>, creator and host of the highly rated CBS series "Keep Well," and publisher of <i>The Change Letter</i>. Dr. Lapp's program, Plant Your Feet Firmly in Mid-Air, is a fast-paced and humorous look at change and the changing conditions of industry and society, with emphasis on accepting, thriving on and creating change.
<p>
<font size=4 color="#2222c2">L</font>uncheon tickets are $35 per person; benefactor-level tickets are $150. Funds raised at this event will benefit women's healthcare at Virginia Mason Medical Center, including its Mobile Mammography Program. Virginia Mason is pleased to recognize Seafirst Bank as a major sponsor of this year's event.
<p>
<font size=4 color="#2222c2">F</font>or reservations or more information on the Women's Advisory Council forum with Janet Lapp, Ph.D., please call Virginia Mason Foundation at (206) 583-6083. Last year's event sold out quickly, so please call early to reserve your seat.
</td>
                <TD COLSTART="3" COLSPAN="1" WIDTH="210" VALIGN="TOP">
<IMG SRC="event01.jpg" border=2><br>
<font size=2><i>Janet Lapp, Ph.D., author and lecturer</i></font>
	</td>
</tr>
