<center><font size=4">DONATIONS AT WORK</font></center>
<p>
<font size=4 color="#2222c2">A</font>s a non-profit organization, Virginia Mason Medical Center relies on the generosity of more than 3,000 individual, corporate, and foundation donors to provide the essential funding necessary to purchase state-of-the-art medical equipment, to create endowed support funds and chairs to retain the top physicians and researchers, and to support annual medical program and research costs.  While operating revenues provide much of the needed funds, philanthropy makes the critical difference in enabling Virginia Mason to continue as leader in the delivery of healthcare for the people of the Pacific Northwest.
