<HTML>

<HEAD>

<TITLE>Virginia Mason - Foundation Tax-Advantaged Giving</TITLE>

</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="back.gif" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000ff" VLINK="#0000ff">

<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="6" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="572">
        <TR>
                <TD COLSTART="1" COLSPAN="1" ROWSTART="2" ROWSPAN="1"VALIGN="TOP">
<IMG SRC="logo2.gif"><IMG SRC="logoc.gif">

                </TD>
                <TD COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="1"  ROWSTART="2" ROWSPAN="1">
	</td>
	</tr>
	</table>



<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="4" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="572">
        <TR>
                <TD COLSTART="1" COLSPAN="1" ROWSTART="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="75" VALIGN="TOP">
                </TD>
                <TD COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="1" WIDTH="497" VALIGN="TOP">
<center>
<font size=4>Estate Planning Vehicles Can Reduce Your Taxes<br>And Provide Charitable Giving Opportunities</font>
</center>
<p>
By selecting any of the following planned giving  opportunities, you will join hundreds of Virginia  Mason Medical Center donors who have already  discovered how to maximize the value of their  estates, maintain financial security, and ensure  the future of the important work carried out at Virginia Mason.
<p>
<font size=4>Wills:</font> A will is a written document that carries out  your wishes at the time of death.<br>
<font size=4>Benefits:</font> Giving to Virginia Mason, a non-profit  organization, in your will may lower your estate  taxes (which can be up to 55%), since the assets  or amount are deducted before the estate tax is  calculated.
<p>
<font size=4>Charitable Gift Annuity:</font> Charitable Gift Annuities  may be established at Virginia Mason Medical  Center in the amount of $10,000 or more.  Annual or quarterly payments are distributed to you  for the remainder of your life. The funds left in the  account at the time of your death benefit programs  at Virginia Mason. <br>
<font size=4>Benefits:</font> If an appreciated asset is used as the  gifting source, you may reduce capital gains taxes  on that asset substantially, in addition to receiving a life income and income tax and estate tax deductions.
<p>
<font size=4>Charitable Remainder Trust:</font> Charitable Remainder  Trusts may be established at Virginia Mason for  $50,000 or more. A Charitable Remainder Trust  may be set up in annuity form, so that you receive  a fixed income for life, or in unitrust form, so that  you receive a set percentage of the value of the  trust, determined annually. <br>
<font size=4>Benefits:</font> You receive a life income and a substantial income tax deduction and may avoid capital gains and estate taxes.
<p>
<font size=4>Charitable Lead Trusts:</font> Charitable Lead Trusts are similar to Charitable Remainder Trusts except you retain the principal for yourself or your family, and Virginia Mason receives the income from these assets for a set number of years. <br>
<font size=4>Benefits:</font> Donors with large estates are able to maximize the amount they pass on to their families by minimizing gift and estate tax. You may also receive an income tax deduction.
<p>
<font size=4>Life Estate:</font> A Life Estate contract specifies Virginia Mason as the recipient of your home at the time of your death. <br>
<font size=4>Benefit:</font> You are entitled to a charitable income tax deduction for the value of your home today while continuing to live in the home for life.
<p>
These are only a few of the many ways planned gifts can benefit you, your family, and Virginia Mason. Your attorney or financial advisor can provide you with details on how charitable planned gifts can work for you. Please call the Virginia Mason Foundation at (206) 583-6083 for additional information.







</TD>
        </TR>
 <TR>
                <TD COLSTART="1" COLSPAN="1" ROWSTART="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="75" VALIGN="TOP">
         </TD>
                <TD COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="2"  ROWSTART="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="490">
<hr>
		</TD>
        </TR>
</TABLE>
