<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Fellowship Opportunities in Regional Anesthesia</TITLE></HEAD>
<! Updated by Kent Hargrave, Virginia Mason Medical Center, Anesthesia Program>
<BODY BACKGROUND="vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="60%">
<img hspace="15" src="vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle"><font size="6">Department of Anesthesiology</font>
<br>
<hr>
<br>
<Table>
<tr>
<td width="40"><img src="blank.gif" alt="" width="40" height="1"></td>
<td>




<center>
<img src="region.jpg" alt="FELLOWSHIP OPPORTUNITIES IN REGIONAL ANESTHESIA">
</center>

<p><br>

The Mason Clinic has a distinguished history of excellence in regional anesthesia. The commitment to teaching regional techniques remains a core aspect of our mission. As such, we offer three different fellowships in regional anesthesia.<p>

	<h4>I.  Regional Anesthesia Fellowship</h4>

	This program trains fellows in operating room applications of regional anesthesia. Over two thirds of anesthetics at VMMC are performed with a regional technique. The fellow becomes experienced in lumbar and thoracic epidurals, subarachnoid blocks, intercostal blocks, and a variety of upper and lower extremity, and other peripheral nerve blocks. Fellows share an equal amount of call with residents. Opportunities for involvement in clinical research projects abound. About one third of fellows go on to enter academic practice. The fellowship is offered for six or twelve months, with most positions being filled with fellows requesting twelve months of experience. Didactics include a specific  fellowship lecture schedule.<p>

	<h4>II.  The Moore / Bridenbaugh Research Fellowship in Regional Anesthesia</h4>

	The Department of Anesthesia offers this two year clinical / research fellowship for those interested in an academic career who wish to develop their research skills.<p>

	<h4>III.  The Astra Fellowship in Regional Anesthesia</h4>

	This three to six month fellowship is designed specifically to train current academic anesthesiologists who desire to upgrade their own regional anesthesia skills. In addition, the program seeks to train the Astra Fellows in techniques for enhancing residency training in regional anesthesia at their home institution.<p>

	  <h4>Stipend and Benefits</h4>

Per annum salary in 1995 is approximately $35,000. Washington State training license, health and dental insurance, and parking are provided. Twenty days are allocated for vacation and professional time.<p>
	

<hr>	
<ul>
<li>Click <a href="fel-app.htm">here</a> to print an application from Netscape 1.1+.
<li>Click <a href="fel-app.doc">here</a> to download a Microsoft Word 6.0 version.
</ul>
<hr>
<h4>For Further Information Contact:</h4>
<blockquote>
Joseph M. Neal, MD<br>
Fellowship Coordinator<br>
Department of Anesthesiology<br>
Virginia Mason Medical Center, B2-AN<br>
PO Box 900<br>
Seattle, WA  98111<br>
206-223-6980<br>
<a href="mailto:anejmn@vmmc.org">anejmn@vmmc.org</a>
</blockquote>

<center>
<h4><a href="index.htm">Return to the VMMC Department of Anesthesiology Home Page</a></h4>
</center>
</td>
</tr>
</table>

