<HEAD>
 <TITLE>VMMC Department of Urology - No Scalpel Vasectomy</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../images/vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="60%">
<img hspace="15" src="../../images/vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle">
<font size=+3><strong>Urology Clinical Fellowship</strong></font>
<p>
<table width=85%>
 <tr>
  <td width="80"><img src="../../images/blank.gif" alt="" width="80" height="1"></td>
</center>
  <td>
<center>
<h2>Urology Clinical Fellowship - July 1998</h2>
</center>
The Section of Urology and Transplantation at Virginia Mason Medical Center in Seattle, Washington, is accepting applications for a one-year clinical fellowship in adult urology.  The fellowship offers an extensive operative experience in all areas of urology, including onocology, renal and pancreas transplantation, reconstructive surgery, urinary incontinence, female urology, urolithiasis, prosthetics and infertility.
<p>
The fellowship is designated to provide four days a week in the operating room, with one protected day a week for reading, writing and preparation for talks.  The fellow also helps supervise resident activity at the Viginia Mason Hospital.  There are seven full-time faculty.
<p>
We are now accepting applications for this fellowship, which starts July 1998.  Applicants should have completed a formal urology residency in the United States, as approved by ACGME, by July 1998.
<pre>

</pre>
<strong><em>Please send CV/letter to:</em></strong><br>
Robert P. Gibbons, M.D.<br>
Urology and Tranplantation, C7-S<br>
Virginia Mason Medical Center<br>
1100 9th Avenue<br>
Seattle, WA  98111<br>
(206) 223-6177<br>
(206) 223-7650 Fax<br>   
<pre>


</pre>
