        <TR>
                <TD COLSTART="1" COLSPAN="1" ROWSTART="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="75" VALIGN="TOP">
                </TD>
                <TD COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="1" WIDTH="287">
<font size=4 color="#2222c2">O</font>ur Cancer Center diagnoses more cancer patients than any other healthcare institution in the Northwest, and <i>Coping</i> magazine has consistently ranked Virginia Mason as <i><b>one of the top 25 cancer treatment centers in the U.S.</i></b>
<p>
<font size=4 color="#2222c2">O</font>ur physicians conduct world-class medical research on breast, prostate, lung, and pancreatic cancer among others through the Virginia Mason Research Center (part of the Medical Center). Through joint studies with Fred Hutchinson and National Cancer Institute - sponsored clinical trial groups, VMMC patients gain access to the newest treatments before they are widely available. <b>Donor support is crucial to ensure that this important work can continue.</b>
</td>
                <TD COLSTART="3" COLSPAN="1" WIDTH="210">
<IMG SRC="cancer01.jpg" border=2><br>
<font size=2><i>The PACCAR Foundation provided a $300,000 grant to renovate and consolidate cancer care services at Virginia Mason to create a more efficient and comfortable treatment system for patients</i></font>
	</td>
</tr>
        <TR>
                <TD COLSTART="1" COLSPAN="1" ROWSTART="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="75" VALIGN="TOP">
                </TD>
                <TD COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="2" WIDTH="497">
<hr>
<font size=4 color="#2222c2">A</font>s a <b>non-profit</b> organization, VMMC relies on the generosity of donors to:
<br>
<IMG SRC="drop.gif" border=0> support vital medical research on cancer,
<br>
<IMG SRC="drop.gif" border=0> provide educational programs for cancer patients and their families,
<br>
<IMG SRC="drop.gif" border=0> sustain our chaplaincy program, which provides emotional support for patients and their families,
<br>
<IMG SRC="drop.gif" border=0> help us make the investment in state-of-the-art   medical equipment like the stereotactic breast needle biopsy machine,
<br>
<IMG SRC="drop.gif" border=0> provide the <i><b>critical funding</i></b> necessary to continue these world-class medical innovations, and
<br>
<IMG SRC="drop.gif" border=0> create named, endowed support funds and chairs to   retain the top physicians and researchers.
<p>
The battle against cancer requires many resources. It requires the most highly trained physicians, nurses, and health care staff available. And it requires <i><b>philanthropy</i></b> to support research for better treatments, education for patients and families, state-of-the-art equipment for diagnosis and treatment, our chaplaincy program for emotional support, and enhancements for patient care needs.
<p>
<center>
<a href="give.htm">Make a Difference in Cancer</a>
</center>
	</TD>
