<HEAD>

<TITLE>Virginia Mason - Foundation Surgical Services</TITLE>

</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="back.gif" BGCOLOR="#ffffff" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#0000ff" VLINK="#0000ff">

<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="2" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="572">
        <TR>
                <TD COLSTART="1" COLSPAN="1" ROWSTART="2" ROWSPAN="1"VALIGN="TOP">
<IMG SRC="logo2.gif"><IMG SRC="logoc.gif">

                </TD>
                <TD COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="1"  ROWSTART="2" ROWSPAN="1">
	</td>
	</tr>
	</table>

<TABLE BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="2" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="572">

        <TR>
                <TD COLSTART="1" COLSPAN="1" ROWSTART="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="75" VALIGN="TOP">
                </TD>
                <TD COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="1" WIDTH="287">
<font size=4 color="#2222c2">V</font>M surgeons have consistently been ranked among the country's leaders in general and specialty surgery.  As a leading referral center for NW hospitals, it is crucial that VM has state-of-the-art surgical equipment to use for our patients.  In 1995, donors supported the purchase of a new microscope for use in ear, nose, and throat surgeries.  This microscope's technological advances include much more intense halogen lights and an additional viewing tube for a second surgeon.
</td>
                <TD COLSTART="3" COLSPAN="1" WIDTH="210">
<IMG SRC="surgery.jpg" border=2><br>
<font size=2><i></i></font>
	</td>
</tr>
        <TR>
                <TD COLSTART="1" COLSPAN="1" ROWSTART="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="75" VALIGN="TOP">
                </TD>
                <TD COLSTART="2" COLSPAN="2" WIDTH="497">
<hr>
<p>
<center>
<font size=4 color="#2222c2">SURGICAL SERVICES AT<br>VIRGINIA MASON MEDICAL CENTER</font>
</center>
<br>
<font size=4 color="#2222c2">F</font>or more than 75 years, Virginia Mason Medical Center physicians have consistently introduced leading edge medicine to the Northwest, beginning with the use of insulin to treat diabetes in the early 1920s. Nuclear medicine, mammography, lithotripsy, stereotactic needle breast biopsy, lung volume reduction surgery, open heart surgery, no-scalpel vasectomy, and cochlear implants all came to this region first under the auspices of Virginia Mason. Because we were the first to introduce these innovations -- and because so many new surgical techniques have been developed  -- Virginia Mason constantly strives to maintain the most up-to-date equipment.
<p>
<font size=4 color="#2222c2">V</font>irginia Mason surgeons have consistently been ranked among the country's leaders in the areas   of general surgery, gynecologic surgery, cardiothoracic surgery, neurosurgery, ophthalmology, orthopaedic surgery, otolaryngology, plastic and reconstructive surgery, and urology and renal transplants. Our kidney transplant program, for example, is regularly ranked among the top 20 in the US, and our cardiac surgery program has mortality rates significantly below the national average. Virginia Mason has done more kidney transplants than all other Northwest hospitals combined. As a leading referral center for Northwest hospitals, it is crucial that Virginia Mason have state-of-the-art surgical equipment to use for our patients. One of Virginia Mason's highest priorities is to find philanthropic support to assist in the purchase of this vital equipment.
<p>
<center>
<a href="give.htm">Make a Difference in Surgical Services</a>
</center>
	</TD>
<tr>
                <TD COLSTART="1" COLSPAN="1" ROWSTART="1" ROWSPAN="1" WIDTH="75" VALIGN="TOP">
