<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>VMMC Anesthesia Fellowship Opportunities In Cardiac Anesthesiology</TITLE></HEAD>
<! Updated by Kent Hargrave, Virginia Mason Medical Center, Anesthesia Program>
<BODY BACKGROUND="vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="60%">
<img hspace="15" src="vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle"><font size="6">Department of Anesthesiology</font>
<br>
<hr>

<Table>
<tr>
<td width="40"><img src="blank.gif" alt="" width="40" height="1"></td>
<td>

<br>
<center>
<img src="Cardiac.jpg" alt="VMMC Anesthesia Cardiac Fellowship">
</center>


<br><br>
The anesthesia fellowship in Cardiac Anesthesiology at Virginia Mason Medical Center is a robust 
twelve month experience in cardiac anesthesiology and intraoperative echocardiography.  One cardiac 
fellow is selected each year for subspecialty training.  The Cardiac Anesthesiology Service provides 
anesthesia for over 500 pump cases each year.  In addition to extensive clinical experience in adult 
cardiac anesthesiology, there is also a minimum of two months training in transthoracic and 
transesophageal echocardiography.  Associated with this fellowship is the opportunity to be engaged in 
clinical research.  Investigations include: evaluation of clinical guidelines, regional anesthesia in cardiac 
surgery, as well as opportunities in clinical pharmacology in cardiac anesthesia.<br><br>


<b><u>Academic Program</u></b><br><br>

<u>Clinical Training</u><br>
The Cardiac Anesthesiology Service provides anesthesia for more than 550 CPB cases per year.  The 
case mix includes approximately 60% CABG, 30% valves with 10% aneurysms and adult congenital.
Operating room support includes:  transesophageal echocardiography with color flow and spectral 
Doppler, ECG with ST segment analysis, mixed venous pulmonary artery oximetry, and fiberoptic 
endoscopy for double lumen tube placement and difficult intubations.<br><br>

<u>Echocardiography</u><br>
One month training in the Division of Cardiology doing transthoracic echocardiography.
One month dedicated supervised experience in transesophageal echocardiography.<br><br>

<u>Conferences</u><br>
There is a weekly cardiac anesthesia conference. This weekly tutorial, involving fellows and residents, 
centers on case presentations, topic discussions, and regular TEE case reviews.<br><br>

<u><b>Optional OR Experiences</b></u><br>
The Department of Anesthesiology at Virginia Mason Medical Center has an international reputation in 
the theory and practice of regional anesthesia.  The Cardiac Anesthesiology Fellow may elect to spend 
some time in regional anesthesia.<br><br>

<b><u>Stipend and benefits</u></b><br>
The per annum salary in 1996 is approximately $38,500.  A Washington State training license, health 
insurance, dental insurance, and parking are provided.  Twenty days are allocated for vacation and 
professional time.<br><br>

<b><u>For further information, contact:</u></b><br>
<dl>
<dt>
<dd>	Keith D. Knopes, M.D.<br>
<dd>	Director, Cardiac Anesthesiology<br>
<dd>	Department of Anesthesiology, B2-AN<br>
<dd>	Virginia Mason Medical Center<br>
<dd>	1100 Ninth Avenue<br>
<dd>	P.O. Box 900<br>
<dd>	Seattle, WA  98111<br><br>
<dd>
<dd>	Phone (206) 223-6980<br>
<dd>	FAX:  (206) 223-6982<br>
<dd>	email:  anekdk@vmmc.org<br>
</dl>
<br><br>
<center>
<h4><a href="index.htm">Return to the VMMC Department of Anesthesiology Home Page</a></h4>
</center>

</td>
</tr>
</table>

