<HEAD>
 <TITLE>VMMC Department of Urology - No Scalpel Vasectomy</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../images/vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="60%">
<img hspace="15" src="../../images/vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle">
<img src="../images/noscapl2.GIF" align="middle">
<pre>
</pre>
<table width=85%>
 <tr>
  <td width="80"><img src="../../images/blank.gif" alt="" width="80" height="1"></td>
</center>
  <td>
<h1>What is a vasectomy?</h1>
	A vasectomy is a surgical procedure that makes a man 
permanently sterile. Virginia Mason urologists are skilled 
in the "no-scalpel vasectomy" procedure, which can be completed 
in about 15 minutes during an office visit. Virginia Mason is a 
leader worldwide in this outpatient surgery.
<pre>

</pre>
<table>
 <tr>
<td><h2><a href="question2.html">Will a vasectomy affect a man's masculinity?</a></h2></td><td><a href="question2.html"><img src="../images/rightarrow.GIF" border=0></a></td>
 </tr>
</table>
