<HTML>
<HEAD>
 <TITLE>VMMC Department of Urology - No Scalpel Vasectomy</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../images/vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="60%">
<img hspace="15" src="../../images/vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle">
<img src="../images/noscapl2.GIF" align="middle">
<pre>
</pre>
<table width=85%>
<tr>
<td width="80"><img src="../../images/blank.gif" alt="" width="80" height="1"></td>
</center>
<td>
<img src="../images/blurb2.gif" align=left>
<h1>Will a vasectomy affect a man's masculinity?</h1>
	Absolutely not. The operation has no effect on the amount of 
sperm produced, the sex drive, the ability to have an 
erection, the amount of semen ejaculated during sex or other male sex 
characteristics. The only effect is that sperm is stopped from 
being ejaculated. 
<p>
In fact, most men find the quality of their sex life is the same or better because they no longer have to worry about pregnancy during sex.
<pre>

</pre>
<table>
 <tr>
<td><h2><a href="question3.html">Who should have a vasectomy?</a></h2></td><td><a href="question3.html"><img src="../images/rightarrow.GIF" border=0></a></td>
 </tr>
</table>
<table>
 <tr>
