<HEAD>
 <TITLE>VMMC Department of Urology - No Scalpel Vasectomy</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../images/vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="60%">
<img hspace="15" src="../../images/vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle">
<img src="../images/noscapl2.GIF" align="middle">
<pre>
</pre>
<table width=85%>
<tr>
<td width="80"><img src="../../images/blank.gif" alt="" width="80" height="1"></td>
</center>
<td>
<h1>Who should have a vasectomy?</h2>
	Men who want to enjoy sex without worrying about pregnancy. 
You should be sure you don't want any more children before 
having a vasectomy. 
<p>
If you are considering a vasectomy, it's 
vital to thoroughly understand that this surgery is 
permanent. (Under certain circumstances, a vasectomy can be surgically 
reversed, but the success of this is not 100 percent 
reliable). Before making the decision, you should discuss it with your 
partner to be certain she won't want children in the future.
<p> 
Proceed with the surgery only when you're confident that it 
is a life-long decision that you will be happy with. Before 
surgery you'll be asked to sign a consent form stating that 
you are aware of the permanence of this surgery.
<pre>

</pre>
<table>
 <tr>
<td><h2><a href="question4.html">How does a vasectomy work?</a></h2></td><td><a href="question4.html"><img src="../images/rightarrow.GIF" border=0></a></td>
 </tr>
