<HEAD>
 <TITLE>VMMC Department of Urology - No Scalpel Vasectomy</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="../../images/vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="60%">
<img hspace="15" src="../../images/vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle">
<img src="../images/noscapl2.GIF" align="middle">
<pre>
</pre>
<table width=85%>
<tr>
<td width="80"><img src="../../images/blank.gif" alt="" width="80" height="1"></td>
</center>
<td>
<img src="../images/blurb3.GIF" align="left">
<h1>What signs should I be aware of?</h1>
	There may be some swelling and bruising in the genital area. 
The is part of the normal healing process. Some aching in 
the testicles can occur for three to twelve weeks. This is due 
to pressure from the trapped sperm and usually resolves itself 
automatically.
<p>
	If you have any questions following the surgery, we invite 
you to call. We also ask you to call if you have a fever or 
severe pain or swelling that is getting worse rather than 
better. This can be a sign of infection or internal 
bleeding.
<pre>
</pre>
