<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Virginia Mason Research Center</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="graphics/vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="80%">
<tr><td><img hspace="15" src="graphics/vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle"></td><td align="left" nowrap><font size="6">Virginia Mason Research Center</font></td></tR></table><p>
<center>

<table width="80%" border="0"><TR><TD width="100"><BR></TD><TD>
The research laboratories at Virginia Mason Research Center focus on molecular and cellular biology of the human immune system, emphasizing the molecular events important in inducing immunity and in pathogenesis of autoimmune diseases such as rheumatoid arthritis and diabetes mellitus. Virginia Mason Research Center scientists also participate in teaching and graduate programs of the <a href="http://www.washington.edu:1180/">University of Washington</a>.<p>
</TD></TR></TABLE>


<img src="graphics/hr.gif"><P>

<table width="80%" border=0>
<tr>
<td rowspan=2>
<img src="graphics/smgn.gif" width="90" height="90" alt=" "></td>
<td><b>
<a href="gnepom.html">Gerald T. Nepom, MD PhD</a><br>
Director<br></b></td></tr>
<tr><td>The Nepom lab explores the molecular basis for initiation and amplification of immunologic events in autoimmunity, 
with emphasis on the critical role of HLA class II genes in the etiology of type I diabetes and rheumatoid arthritis.<P></td></tr>

<tr>
<td rowspan=2>
<img src="graphics/smpc.gif" width="90" height="90" alt=" "></td>
<td><b>
<a href="patcon.html">Pat Concannon, PhD</a><br>
Associate Member<br></b></td></tr>
<tr><td>Genetic susceptibilty to diabetes and cancer; 
immunogenetics of human T cell receptor genes.<P></td></tr>

<tr>
<td rowspan=2>
<img src="graphics/smem.gif" width="90" height="90" alt=" "></td>
<td><b>
<a href="emilner.html">Eric C. B. Milner, PhD</a><br>
Associate Member<br></b></td></tr>
<tr><td>Molecular biology of immunoglobulin genes and the B cell, 
autoimmunity, immunoregulation.<P></td></tr>

<tr>
<td rowspan=2>
<img src="graphics/smbn.gif" width="90" height="90" alt=" "></td>
<td><b>
<a href="bnepom.html">Barbara S. Nepom, MD</a><br>
Research Associate Member<br></b></td></tr>
<tr><td>Immunogenetics of adult and pediatric rheumatic diseases, 
regulation and peptide binding of human major histocompatibility complex 
molecules, autoimmunity.<P></td></tr>


<tr>
<td rowspan=2>
<img src="graphics/smbk.gif" width="90" height="90" alt=" "></td>
<td><b>
<a href="bkwok.html">William W. Kwok, PhD</a><br>
Research Assistant Member<br></b></td></tr>
<tr><td>Structural and functional studies of class II molecules and T cell 
receptors, gene expression using retroviral vectors.<P></td></tr></table>

