<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>VMRC - Patrick J. Concannon</TITLE></HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="graphics/vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="80%">
<tr><td><img hspace="15" src="graphics/vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle"></td>
<td align="left" nowrap><font size="5">Virginia Mason Research Center<br>
Patrick J. Concannon</font></td></tR></table><p>

<center>

<table border="0">

<TR>

<td valign="top">
<img src="graphics/lgpc.jpg" ><p>
</td>

<TD>
Research in Dr. Concannon's laboratory focuses on the 
genetics of several different human disorders. These include ataxia
telangiectasia (AT), a rare cancer susceptibility/radiation sensitivity 
disorder, insulin-dependent diabetes mellitus 
(IDDM), an autoimmune disease in which the insulin-secreting islet cells
of the pancreas are destroyed, and non-insulin dependent diabetes mellitus
(NIDDM), a metabolic disorder in which the ability to secrete in the pancreas
and the ability to respond to insulin in peripheral tissues are both 
disrupted. Additional, non-disease related projects in the laboratory focus
on the structure and function of human T cell receptors for antigen.
</td>


</tr>
</table>
<p>
<img src="graphics/hr.gif">
<p>


