Hansen, J. A., Radka, S. F., and Nepom, G. T.  Structural requirements for 
recognition of the HLA-DW14 class II epitope -- a key HLA determinant 
associated with rheumatoid arthritis.  Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. USA, 
87:8051-8055, 1990.<P>
          
Kwok, W. W., Kovats, S., Thurtle, P., and Nepom, G. T.  HLA-DQ allelic 
polymorphisms constrain patterns of class II heterodimer formation.  
J. Immunol. 150:2263-2272, 1993.<P>

Bauer, T.R., Jr., Osborne, W.R.A., Kwok, W.W., and Hickstein, D.D.  
Expression from leukocyte integrin promoters in retroviral vectors.  
Human Gene Therapy 5:709-716, 1994.<P>

Hock, R.A., Reynolds, B.D., Tucker-McClung, C.L., and Kwok, W.W.  Cure of 
mice bearing lethal neuroblastoma by vaccination with cells retrovirally 
transduced to expression human class II major histocompatibility complex 
genes.  J. Immunotherapy, 17:12-18, 1995.<P>

Kwok, W.W., Nepom, G.T., Raymond, F.C.  HLA-DQ polymorphisms are highly 
selective for peptide binding interactions.  J. Immunol. 155: 2468-2476, 
1995.<P>

Kwok, W.W, Domeier, M., Johnson, M., Nepom, G.T., and Koelle, D. HLA-DQB1 
codon 57 is a critical determinant of peptide binding and recognition. 
J. Exp. Med., 1996, in press.<P>

Kwok, W. W., Domeier,  M., Raymond, F., Byers, P., and Nepom, G.T. 
Allele-specific motifs  characterize HLA-DQ interactions iwht a 
diabetes-associated peptide derived from  glutamic acid decarboxylase. 
J. Immuno., 1996, in press.<P>





<P>
</td>
