<b>
<center>
<h2>The Ataxia-Telangiectasia Mutation Database</h2>
<h3>Explanation of the Tables</h3>
</center>

<blockquote>
Nomenclature for mutation listings is based on the suggestions of Beaudet and Tsui
(Hum Mutat 2:245-248, 1993) and <a href="http://ariel.ucs.unimelb.edu.au:80/~cotton/antonara.htm">Antonarakis</a>.
Nucleotide numbering is based on the sequence from Savitsky et al. (Hum Mol Gen 4:2025-2032, 1995).
The first nucleotide of the initiation codon has been taken as nucleotide #1.
Intron/exon boundaries are as defined by Uziel et al. (Genomics 33:317-320, 1996).<P>
Total mutations are reported even though some may reflect founder effects.
When available, mutations detected in genomic DNA are given priority over reports of alterations in cDNA.
When multiple laboratories have reported the same mutations in the same cell line, only a single reference has been provided as an example.
While we have tried to cite the first available reference in each of these cases, users should recognize that the referencing is <i>not</i> intended to be exhaustive, nor to reflect some priority in discovery.<P>
</blockquote>
