<center><table width=80%>
 <tr><td><center><b><h3>Community Clinic Opportunities</h3></b></center></td></tr>
 <tr><td><font size=2>Senior residents in the second and third year of training have opportunities to build their own practice at one of our community clinic sites, adding this experience one half day per week to their IMA continuity clinic practice. The residents' care of patients in all these locations is supervised by highly qualified generalists.  The CarolynDowns Clinic Family Medical Center is a neighborhood health center located on Capital Hill in Seattle.  Virginia Mason residents join other providers to care for predominately indigent, Englisn-speaking African-American and Mexican-American patients and families.<br>
<br>
The International Medical Community Health Center is located in central Seattle and serves an Asian population of patients, many non-English speaking.  Full time, on-site interpreters facilitate communication.<br>
<br>
The Pike Marker Medical Clinic is located in the Pike Market on the waterfront in Seattle. Serving predominately an indigent, often homeless population, this clinic has served as a site for continuity practice for Virginia Mason residents for more than 10 years.<br>
<br>
The Rainier Park Medical Clinic, located in the Central District in Seattle, is one of seven county-funded neighborhood health centers caring for an under-served, indigent population. Many patients are African-American, Mexican-American, or Asian.
</td></tr>
</font></table></center>

<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center><br>
<center><table width=80%>
     <tr><td><b><h3><center>Special Opportunities</center></h3></b></td></tr>
     <tr><td><font size=2>Opportunities exist for residents to arrange electives overseas.  Through our institution's commitment to the Pacific Rim and our International Medicine Department, some of our residents have arranged experiences in Korea, China, Hong Kong, Malaysia, Indonesia, and India.<br>
<br>
An integral part of our Internal Medicine curriculum is learning to be cost-effective and efficient in providing services to your patients.  We are committed to teaching you these skills as a habit that will serve you well in your future practice.<br>
<br>
You will also have opportunities to work with experts in managed care during your training.  Our Alliance with Group Health Cooperative of Puget Sound provides many exciting educational opportunities for learning the concepts of population health management.<br>
<br>
Like many health care centers, our organization is committed to the process of Continuous Quality Improvement.  During yourtraining at VirginiaMason Medical Center, you will have an opportunity to work on value improvement teams and learn how to apply the principles of CQI to your daily work in health care.

</font></td></tr>  
</table></center><br>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center><br>
<center><table width=80%>
     <tr><td><b><h3><center>Evaluation and Feedback</center></h3></b></td></tr>
     <tr><td><font size=2>While at Virginia Mason you will have an opportunity to evaluate all aspects of the residency program, both formally and informally.  We welcome our residents' criticisms and ideas and see this feedback as a key element for continually improving our program to meet our residents' needs.<br>
<br>
Medicine residents meet formally with the Program Director for performance evaluations at least twice yearly. Residents may meet with the program director at any time formally or informally. Residents are evaluated on a monthly basis by their faculty.<br>
<br>
Residents are given the opportunity for self-evaluation prior to their periodic discussion with the program director of intermediate learning goals and long term professional plans.<br>
<br>
Inquiries regarding the Internal Medicine Program at Virginia Mason Medical Center should be directed to:
</font></td></tr>  
</table></center><br>
<center><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="75%">

             <tr><td width=55%><h5>Roger W. Bush, M.D.<BR> 
                                        Program Director in Internal Medicine <BR>                                               
                                        Virginia Mason Medical Center<BR>
                                        Office of Housestaff Affairs, H8-ME<BR>
                                        925 Seneca Street <BR>
                                        Seattle. Wa 98101  <BR>
                                       <a href="mailto:gimrwb@vmmc.org">gimrwb@vmmc.org</a></h5></td></tr>
</table></center>

<center><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="75%">
