<center><table width=80%>
<tr><td colspan=2><fontsize=2>The Internal Medicine Residency Program has a written curriculum that guides the educational program for each resident.  The curriculum is a dynamic, evolving document that responds to changes in the health care environment, changes in the learning needs of the residents, and changes in the expectations of the residents' future practice needs.  The topic-based curriculum is divided into three sections.  Each curriculum chapter lists specific learning objectives for that topic. The curriculum<i> Table of Contents </i>is listed here:</font></td></tr>           
</table></center><br>
<br>
<hr width=80%>
<center><table border=2><tr><td>
