</table></center>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center><br>
<center><table width=80%>
 <tr><td><font size=2>
Daily conferences are integrated to present both didactic and practical coverage of surgical problems.  The conferences and ward rounds are directed toward resident education and are delivered both by the staff and the residents.  Surgical Journal Club is held 2 times a month, based on the "SELECTED READINGS" Series from Southwestern Medical Center at Dallas and a monthly installment of current journal articles.  These papers are provided for all categorical surgical residents.  In addition, residents are provided with SESAP (Surgical Education and Self-Assessment Program), the learning program written by the American College of Surgeons.  Each year, all residents are required to take the American Board of Surgery In-Training Examination (ABSITE).  Our faculty also holds mock oral examinations for the surgical housestaff in order to prepare them for the American Board of Surgery Oral Examination.  Each Tuesday morning, a multiple choice test is administered by the Chief Resident to all residents. The test is based on readings from a current textbook of surgery and covers the entire field of surgery.  In addition, residents are encouraged to prepare individually for each case by reading a textbook description, a surgical atlas and an anatomy text.  
<br><br>
During the residency, each resident is expected to co-author scientific papers with attending surgical staff and to present research at local, regional, and national surgical meetings.  A travel policy for residents presenting papers is an integral part of the program.  A list of recent publications and presentations by our surgical residents is enclosed.  
<br><br>
Inquiries regarding the surgical residency program at Virginia Mason Medical Center should be directed to: 
</font></table></center>
<center><TABLE WIDTH="50%">

                     <tr><td><h5>Richard Thirlby, M.D.<BR> 
                                        Program Director, General surgery Residency, <BR>                                         
                                        Virginia Mason Medical Center<BR>
