<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center><br>

<center><img align="center" src="benefit.gif"></center>
<br>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center><br>

<center><table width=70%>
<tr><td width=5%><font size=4>1.</font></td>
      <td width=30%><font size=4>Stipends</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td><font size=2>R-1</font></td><td width=60%><font size=2>$30,502</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td><font size=2>R-2</font></td><td width=60%><font size=2>$33,523</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td><font size=2>R-3</font></td><td width=60%><font size=2>$34,237</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td><font size=2>R-4</font></td><td width=60%><font size=2>$36,369</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td><font size=2>R-5</font></td><td width=60%><font size=2>$38,985</font></td></tr>
</table></center>
<hr width=75%>

<center><table width=70%>
<tr><td width=5%><font size=4>2.</font></td>
      <td width=45%><font size=4>Moving Allowance</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td colspan=3 width=95%><font size=2>Financial assistance to aid with moving expenses for appointees of one year minimum to Virginia Mason Medical Center's staff has been established with the following mileage schedule:</font></td></tr>
<tr><td width=5%></td><td width=45%><font size=2>150 - 300 Miles</font></td>
                    <td width=50%><font size=2>$50.00</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td><font size=2>301-600 miles</font></td>
                    <td><font size=2>$75.00</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td><font size=2>601 -1,000 miles</font></td>
                    <td><font size=2>$100.00</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td><font size=2>1,001-1,400miles</font></td>
                    <td><font size=2>$200.00</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td><font size=2>1,401-1,800 miles</font></td>
                    <td><font size=2>$300.00</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td><font size=2>1,801-2,200 miles</font></td>
                    <td><font size=2>$400.00</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td><font size=2>2,201 Plus miles</font></td>
                    <td><font size=2>$500.00</font></td></tr>

</table></center>
<hr width=75%>
<center><table width=70%>
<tr><td width=5%><font size=4>3.</font></td>
      <td width=45%><font size=4>Vacations</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td colspan=3 width=95%><font size=2>All residents for one year will receive three  weeks of vacation per year</font></td></tr>
</table></center>

<hr width=75%>
<center><table width=70%>
<tr><td width=5%><font size=4>4.</font></td>
      <td width=45%><font size=4>Medical Insurance</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td colspan=3 width=95%><font size=2>Comprehensive medical insurance is provided to housestaff members and their dependents with the premium paid by the Medical Center.  The resident has the option of several dental insurance plans.  A life insurance policy with a face value of $20,000 and long-term disability insurance will be provided to the resident staff, with the premium paid by the Medical Center.
</font></td></tr>
</table></center>
<hr width=75%>

<center><table width=70%>
<tr><td width=5%><font size=4>5.</font></td>
      <td width=45%><font size=4>Malpractice Insurance</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td colspan=3 width=95%><font size=2>
The Medical Center provides malpractice insurance coverage at no cost to the housestaff member. Such malpractice insurance coverage is limited, however, to the performance of duties at, or approved by, Virginia Mason Medical Center.
</font></td></tr>
</table></center>
<hr width=75%>

<center><table width=70%>
<tr><td width=5%><font size=4>6.</font></td>
      <td width=45%><font size=4>Meals</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td colspan=3 width=95%><font size=2>
Breakfast and dinner will be provided for the housestaff member on duty.
</font></td></tr>
</table></center>
<hr width=75%>

<center><table width=70%>
<tr><td width=5%><font size=4>7.</font></td>
      <td width=45%><font size=4>Uniforms</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td colspan=3 width=95%><font size=2>

White coats will be provided for all members of the resident staff.
</font></td></tr>
</table></center>
<hr width=75%>

<center><table width=70%>
<tr><td width=5%><font size=4>8.</font></td>
      <td colspan=2width=5%><font size=4>
Meeting Time</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td colspan=2 width=95%><font size=2>
Residents are eligible for financial assistance to attend medical meetings.  To be eligible to receive financial assistance, the following criteria apply</font></td></tr>
<tr><td width=5%></td><td><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td><td width=95%><font size=2> Residency appointment must be for minimum of a one-year duration.</font></td></tr>
<tr><td width=5%></td><td  valign=top><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td><td width=95%><font size=2> Residents presenting a paper at a meeting within the continental United States will have reimbursement for expenses, usually coach class fare, plus per diem consistent with that allowed by the Medical Center. </font></td></tr>
<tr><td width=5%></td><td  valign=top><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td><td width=95%><font size=2> Residents will be eligible to attend medical meetings without presenting a paper and be reimbursed at a rate of $200 per year of residency tenure at Virginia Mason Medical Center. </font></td></tr> 
<tr><td width=5%></td><td  valign=top><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td><td width=95%><font size=2>Prior approval for all assistance must be obtained by consent of both the Program Director and the Director of Medical Education. </font></td></tr> 

</table></center>
<hr width=75%>

<center><table width=70%>
<tr><td width=5%><font size=4>9.</font></td>
      <td width=45%><font size=4>Housestaff Discretionary Fund </font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td colspan=3 width=95%><font size=2>$2,400 per year is donated by Virginia Mason Medical Center to the Discretionary Fund to be used as the resident staff desire
</font></td></tr>
</table></center>
</table></center>
<hr width=75%>

<center><table width=70%>
<tr><td width=5%><font size=4>10.</font></td>
      <td width=45%><font size=4>State Licensure </font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td colspan=3 width=95%><font size=2>The Medical Center pays the initial and renewal fees for licensure in the State of Washington.  Two years of postgraduate training are required for permanent licensure in the State of Washington.
</font></td></tr>
</table></center>

<hr width=75%>

<center><table width=70%>
<tr><td width=5%><font size=4>11.</font></td>
      <td width=45%><font size=4>Parking </font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td colspan=3 width=95%><font size=2>
Parking for all members of the housestaff is provided by the Medical Center.
</font></td></tr>
</table></center>
<hr width=75%>

<center><table width=70%>
<tr><td width=5%><font size=4>12.</font></td>
      <td width=45%><font size=4>Xeroxing </font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td><td colspan=3 width=95%><font size=2>
Xeroxing of material for educational purposes of the housestaff will be provided by the Medical Center.
</font></td></tr>
</table></center>
<hr width=75%>

<center><table width=70%>
<tr><td width=5%><font size=4>13.</font></td>
      <td colspan=2><font size=4>Leave Policy</font></td>
<tr><td></td width=5%><td  valign=top><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td>
                   <td><font size=2>Sick leave = 30 days per year.</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td width=5%><td  valign=top><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td>
                   <td><font size=2> Emergency leave = 7 days per year.</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td width=5%><td  valign=top><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td>
                   <td><font size=2> Childcare leave = 6 weeks..</font></td></tr>
<tr><td></td width=5%><td  valign=top><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td>
                   <td><font size=2> eave without pay = up to 12 weeks.</font></td></tr>
