<head>
<title>Mobile Mammography </title>

</head>
<BODY BACKGROUND="vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">

<table cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2" width="85%">
<tr>
<td><img hspace="15" src="vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle"></td>
<td align="center"><img align="center" src="vrad.gif"></td></TR>
</TABLE>
<CENTER><B><H1>Mobile Mammography</B></H1></CENTER>
<center>
<img src="mobvan.gif">
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="corp.gif"></center>
<br><img src="vmbbarw.gif" >
<br></center>
<center><table WIDTH="65%">
<tr><td width=70%><h3><i>In about the time it takes for a coffee break, women at your                                 workplace can take a simple test to reduce health care costs, lower absenteeism, provide peace of mind, and possibly save their lives</i></h3>.</td>
           <td width=40%><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="mampic2.gif"></td>
</tr></table></center>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center>

<CENTER><H2>Let Us Bring Health Care<BR>
                        to Your Front Door</H2></CENTER>

<center><table  WIDTH="85%">
<tr><td><fontsize=3>Virginia Mason Medical Center understands that healthy employees mean a healthier workforce.  To assist with your efforts to create a healthy workplace, we offer state-of-the-art mammography screening opportunities to your organization at the location of your choice.
<BR><BR>
While mobile screening vans are a new concept in health care, they bring the same technologies you'll find at our hospital and clinics.  In fact, certification and quality control for our screening procedures meet or exceed state and professional standards. </font></td</tr>
</table></center>
<CENTER><H2>Early Detection Saves Lives</H2></CENTER>

<center><table WIDTH="85%">
<tr><td colspan=2>Women have a one in nine estimated lifetime risk of developing breast cancer--it's the most common form of cancer among women and the rates are rising.  Thanks to mammography we can identify breast cancer at its earliest and most curable stage--up to two years before a lump can be detected by a woman or by her physician.  When breast cancers are detected early, nearly 100 percent of the cases can be treated successfully.<BR><BR>

Screening for pre-menopausal women is in continuous review: Virginia Mason recommends women consult with their health care provider to decide what's right for them.  The American Cancer Society offers the following guidelines for consideration:</td></tr>
</table></center>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center>
<center><table WIDTH="65%">
<tr><td  valign=top width=40% ><H4>Regular Mammograms:</H3></td><td width=70%><H4>Begin screening mammograms by age 40<BR>Have one every 1-2 years to age 49<BR>Annually after age 50</H4></tr></td>
</table></center>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center>
<center><table WIDTH="65%">
<tr><td  valign=top width=40% ><H4>Clinical Breast Exams:</H3></td><td width=70%><H4>Have one every three years between the ages of 20 and 40<BR>Annualy after age 40</tr></td>
</table></center>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center>
<center><table WIDTH="65%">
<tr><td  valign=top width=40% ><H4>Brease Self-Exams:</H3></td><td width=80%><H4>Monthly beginning at age 20</H4></tr></td>
</table></center>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center>

<center><table width=85%><tr><td colspan =3>Virginia mason's mobile mammography van offers the same comfort you'd find at our hospital or clinics:</td></tr>
<tr><td width=5%></td><td valign=top width=5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></td><td>Friendly female Staff</td></tr>
<tr><td width=20%></td><td valign=top width=5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></td><td>Private and comfortable environment</td></tr>
<tr><td width=20%></td><td valign=top width=5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></td><td>American College of Radiology certified technologists and Board certified radiologists</td></tr>
<tr><td width=20%></td><td valign=top width=5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></td><td>ACR and FDA approved equipment</td></tr>
<tr><td width=20%></td><td valign=top width=5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></td><td>Results directed to physician of choice</td></tr>
<tr><td width=20%></td><td valign=top width=5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></td><td>Insurance Billing Available</td></tr>
</table></center>
<CENTER><H2>Good Health is Good Business</H2></CENTER>
<center><table width=85%>
<tr><td width=5%></td><td valign=top width=5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></td><td>Allows working women easy access to routine screening</td></tr>
<tr><td width=20%></td><td valign=top width=5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></td><td>Minimizes off site medical appointment</td></tr>
<tr><td width=20%></td><td valign=top width=5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></td><td>Enhances employee relations</td></tr>
<tr><td width=20%></td><td valign=top width=5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></td><td>Provides health education opportunity for employees</td></tr>
</table></center>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center><BR>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="gift.gif"></center><BR>
<center><table WIDTH="85%"><tr><td><H3></H3>Getting a mammogram is one thing every woman can do about breast cancer.  Offering a workplace screening is one thing every employer can do to save lives from breast cancer - at no direct billing to most insurance companies and provide you with materials such as employee information packets, posters and newsletter ads to make your screening a success.  We'll even provide a free cup of coffee to all participants!<BR><BR>
For 75 years Virginia Mason has been a nationally recognized health care leader, providing quality primary and specialty care to people in the Pacific Northwest.  Saving lives from breast cancer is important to us.  Our mobile health services staff is eager to provide the program right for your organization.</td></tr>
</table></center><BR>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center><BR>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="satmob.gif"></center><BR>
<center><table WIDTH="85%">
<tr><td valign=top ><fontsize=3>
Mobile Mammography service was started in March of 1995. The
van performed over 1,380 mammograms in its first ten months of service.
<br>
<br>The Van aslo services our new satellites with Mammography:
</font></td>
</tr>
</table></center>
<center><table  WIDTH="75%">
<tr>
