<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Residents </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">
<table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="60%">
<img hspace="15" src="vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle"><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vrad.gif"><br>

<center>
<br><img src="radres2.gif" alt="VMMC Radiology Residency">
</center>
<center><HR  SIZD=3 width=65%></center>
<center><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="80%">
<tr>
     <td><h4> The Radiology Residency at Virginia Mason is the oldest approved Radiology residency in the Northwest.  We have always been fully accredited with our most recent review in 1995 leading to the maximum five year approval of our residency program.
</h4></td></tr>
</table></center>
<center><HR  SIZD=3 width=65%></center>
<CENTER><H2><B><I>Strengths of our program</I></B></H2></CENTER>
<center><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="75%">
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>
              <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%> <h4>  Large volume radiology department covering the full range of radiology                    including interventional radiology, MRI, CT, and vascular and obstetrical ultrasound</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>
              <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%><h4> State of the art equipment throughout the department.</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>
              <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%><h4> Excellent clinical cases due to our mixture of tertiary referral cases                                                        from throughout the Northwest and our large primarycare population.</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>
              <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%><h4>Unusually strong working relationship between the Radiology Department and                                      our excellent clinical departments.</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>
              <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%><h4>Full Lecture Series for radiology residents:</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td></td>
             <Td valign=top width = 5%></Td>
                 <td width =95%><h4>2 lectures or conferences per day at this instution</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td></td>
             <Td valign=top width = 5%></Td>
                   <td width =95%><h4> Attendance at the Thursday afternoon lecture series at the University of                                            Washington:</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td></td>
             <Td valign=top width = 5%></Td>
                 <td width =95%><h4> Introductory lecture series for first year residents during July and August:</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>
              <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%><h4> Extensive hands-on exposure due to large volume and no                                              fellows.</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>
               <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%><h4> Excellent teaching file including ACR video disc teaching file.</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>
               <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%><h4>Teaching style - challenging but supportive and friendly</h4></td></tr>.
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>
              <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%><h4> Committed active teaching staff, many from former academic                                                                 positions.</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>
              <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%><h4> Active program directors with Dr. Peterson currently the President of the                                                          Association of Program Directors in Radiology.</h4></td></tr>
</table></center>
<center><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="80%">
      <td><h4>The radiology residency is one of five residencies in this institution.  We currently have 100 Virginia Mason residents total (Internal Medicine, Surgery, Anesthesia, Radiology and Transitional Internship) with additional residents and fellows rotating from programs at theUniversity of Washington.</h4></td></tr>
</table></center>
<center><HR  SIZD=3 width=65%></center>
<CENTER><H3><b><i>    Overall Mission</i></b></h3></CENTER>

<center><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="75%">              
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>          
              <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%><h4> To train physicians to be superb radiologists capable of proceeding directly                                        to private practice or to enter fellowships that lead to academic or privatepractice.</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>
               <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%><h4> To produce radiologists who attain certification by the American Board of                                      Radiology.</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>
              <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%><h4> To train residents with strong organizational skills and the ability to direct                                             self education during and following residency.</h4></td></tr>
<tr>    <Td valign=top width = 5%><IMG ALIGN=top SRC="blueball.gif"></Td>
                          <td COLSPAN=2 width =95%><h4> To produce radiologists with high ethical standards.</h4></td></tr>
</table></center>
<center><HR  SIZD=3 width=65%></center>
<CENTER><H3><b><i>Positions Available:</i></b></h3></CENTER>
<center><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="80%">
<tr><td><h4>
Through the National Resident Matching Program, we offer a complete Diagnostic Radiology Residency including a transitional year internship at Virginia Mason Medical Center.  We havetwo residency positions for each of the PGY-1 through PGY-5 years.  Doing  the internship at Virginia Mason allows exposure to all the other housestaff and clinicians.  This makes the transition to Radiology much easier since one is already familiar with the workings of themedical center.  The small size of our residency allows a very close working relationship between residents and attending staff.
</h4></td></tr>
</table></center>
<HR>
<center><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="80%">
<tr><td><h4>
                Inquiries regarding the radiology residency at Virginia Mason Medical Center should be
                Directed to:
</h4></td></tr>
</table></center>
