<TR ALIGN=LEFT><Td VALIGN=TOP>7:45 Rad Dept<BR> Conf<BR>12:30 Angio<BR> Lecture<Td VALIGN=TOP>7:30 MR Ortho<BR> Conf<BR>12:30 GU<BR> Lecture</td><Td VALIGN=TOP>7:00 GU Conf<BR>12:30 Resident<BR> Case Conf</td><Td VALIGN=TOP>7:30 Neuro <BR>Conf<BR>12:30 Mock<BR> Oral Conf<BR>3:00 UW Conf</td><Td VALIGN=TOP>7:30 Grand Rounds</td></TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>
<br><HR  SIZD=3>
<pre><CENTER><H3><b><i>Fellowship Training</i></b></h3></CENTER></pre>
<PRE><H4>      

                 After completing our program approximately half our residents proceed to a variety of
                 fellowships. Below is a list of fellowships that our residents completed in the last five years.

                 1996     Angio/Interventional Fellowship at U of New Mexico
                              MR Research Fellowship at UW

                 1995     MR Fellowship at Mallinckrodt

                 1993     US Fellowship at UC San Diego
                              MR Fellowship at Cedars/ Sinai - UCLA

                 1992    Body Imaging Fellowship at UW

                 1991    US Fellowship at Sweedish Hospital, Seattle

<center><HR  SIZD=3 width=65%></center>
<pre><CENTER><H3><b><i>Practice after Graduation</i></b></h3></CENTER></pre>
<PRE><H4>      

                 Most of our residents enter private practice either directly after residency or after completing
                 a fellowship but a number are in academics.  Examples of practice choices in the last five years
                 include:

                 1996     Large (30 radiologists) private practice in North Carolina

                 1995     Small private practice group in Port Angeles, WA.
                              Larger private practice in Seattle

                 1994     Large private practice group in California
                              HMO (Group Health) in Seattle area

                 1993     Virginia Mason Radiology Dept.
                              UW Radiology Dept.

                1992	 Multispecialty Clinic in Spokane
                              Private practice in Idaho
</H4></PRE>
<center><HR  SIZD=3 width=65%></center>
<pre><CENTER><H3><b><i>Evaluation and Feedback</i></b></h3></CENTER></pre>
<center><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="85%">
<tr>
     <td><h4>
                At the end of each rotation the residents are asked to fill out evaluation forms on both
                the attending staff and the rotation itself.  The Program Directors then compile these
                evaluations and review them annually with the appropriate teaching coordinators.  We
                value our residents' feedback and utilize this information to continually improve our
                program.  Changes are implemented quickly and the response time to residents' suggestions
                is quite short.

                Radiology residents meet formally with the Program Director at least every six months to
                review their performance evaluations.  Residents are evaluated after each rotation by the
                faculty.  A summary of his or her evaluations is discussed with each individual resident.
                Learning goals for the next six months and long term professional goals are discussed at 
                these sessions.
</h4></td></tr>
</table></center>
