<TITLE> Segmented Hub</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BACKGROUND="vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">
<table cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2" width="85%">
<tr>
<td><img hspace="15" src="vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle"></td>
<td align="center"><img align="center" src="vrad.gif"></td></TR>
</TABLE ></CENTER>
<CENTER><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="pacs.gif"></CENTER><I></I>
<H1><CENTER><B>Network</B></CENTER></H1>
<HR size="3" width="85%">
<center><TABLE width ="85%">
<tr>
<td valign=top ><H5>The department of Radiology at the Virginia Mason Medical Center
has been in the process of developing a Picture Archiving and 
Communication System for the last five years.  This endeavor  resulted in the 
construction of a "Central Cable Plant" room in order to consolidate  our connections to one
central location.  <BR><BR>
The network consists of each modality interconnected by 10mb/s ethernet
hubs all of which in turn are connected to an ethernet switch.  The CR system
from ICU and CCU, the physician workstations and laser printers 
are all connected directly to Hi Speed Switch ports.<BR><BR>
Our cabling consists of twenty two miles of Level 5 unshielded twisted pair.
There are a minimum of two RJ45 connections in every room of the Radiology Department, one connected to the imaging network, the other to the IS network. <BR><BR>


.</h5>  
<td ><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="segment.gif"></td>
</TR>
</table></center>
