<HEAD>
<TITLE>ltrasound </TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BODY BACKGROUND="vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">
<table cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2" width="85%">
<tr>
<td><img hspace="15" src="vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle"></td>
<td align="center"><img align="center" src="vrad.gif"></td>
</TR></TABLE></CENTER>
<CENTER><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="pacs.gif"></CENTER>
<H1><CENTER><B>Ultrasound Network</B></CENTER></H1>
<HR size="3" width="85%">

<center><TABLE width ="85%">
<tr>
<td valign=top ><H5>The Ultrasound department participated in the development of a PACS system with an ultrasound vendor.  The project started three years ago and upgrades continue to be tested.  .  <BR><BR>
The ultrasound network consists of each ultrasound unit interconnected by a 10mb/s ethernet
hub.  The Hub is connected to the High Speed Switch for rapid transmission of images to a laser printer..<BR><BR>
In January of 1995, Ultrasound was the first imaging section of Radiology to become "filmless".   This has provided the rest of the department with valuable information for future projects.  This project also pointed out quite clearly the gains in staff productivity (savings of nine minutes per examination) as well as reduced supply costs (film, processing, etc).<BR><BR>
</h5>  
<td ><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="ult2.gif"></td></tr></table></center>
<HR size="3" width="65%">
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="ultnetg.gif"></center>
