<H1><CENTER><B>Ultrasound Wide Area Network</B></CENTER></H1>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center>
<BR>
<center><table width=85%><tr valign=top><td width =50%><h5>The Ultrasound department extended their services to the satellites in the summer of 1995 by installing their first WAN (wide area network) to the Virginia Mason East satellite Clinic. <BR><BR>
 The LAN (local area network) is connected to the WAN by means of a T-1 line between  hubs of the two networks. <BR><BR> 
There are two additional pieces of equipment that are needed in order to this to happen.  Shown at the right are representations of a CSU/DSU and Router, and how they are used to connect the networks and T-1 lines together.  The CSU/DSU and Router are not shown on the image below this description.</h5></td>
