<head>
<title> </title>
</head>
<BODY BACKGROUND="vmbg.gif" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" TEXT="#00000">

<table cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2" width="85%">
<tr>
<td><img hspace="15" src="vmsqlog2.jpg" align="middle"></td>
<td align="center"><img align="center" src="vrad.gif"></td></TR>
</TABLE>
<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center>
<CENTER><h2><img align=bottom src="chief.gif"></h2></CENTER>

<center><table width="85%"><tr><td>I extend a personal welcome to the Internet site of the Radiology Department at Virginia Mason Medical Center, Seattle, Washington.  The Radiology Departments <a href="mission.htm">mission</a> is to provide accurate, efficient, cost effective, timely diagnostic information and therapeutic procedures which enable medical care providers meet the needs of their patients. <br><br> 

Our reputation for excellence stems from our ability to arrive quickly at an accurate diagnosis with minimum diagnostic testing.  We work closely with our referring providers to correlate clinical information and create a diagnostic plan that will lead to the diagnosis efficiently without the need for patients to return for additional imaging tests.  We strive to complete the diagnostic imaging workup in one day whenever possible.  <br><br>

Virginia Masons Radiology department is well situated for <a href="pacs.htm">digital imaging</a> through an installed Ethernet network.   As all modalities become DICOM compatible, we will be able to move images from one modality to another, and view the images on diagnostic workstations.   At some point we intend to move images and reports to the clinical side of the medical centers networks.  
</td></tr></table></center>
<center><table width="75%"><tr><td colspan=2><b><i>The department is divided into several                                                                                      sections</i></b></td></tr>
	<tr><td width=5%><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td>
                       <td><a href="general.htm">General Diagnosis (Xray)</a></td></tr>
	<tr><td><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td>
                                        <td><a href="mammo.htm"> Breast Diagnosis                                                       (Mammography)</a></td></tr>
              <tr><td><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td>
                                        <td><a href="mobmam1.htm">Mobile Mammography</a></td></tr>
	<tr><td><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td>    
                                        <td><a href="ct.htm"> Computed Tomography (CT)</a></td></tr>  
	<tr><td><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td>    
                                        <td><a href="mri.htm"> Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI)</a></td></tr>  
	<tr><td><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td>   
                                         <td><a href="ultra.htm">Ultrasound</a> </td></tr>  
	<tr><td><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td>   
                                         <td><a href="nucmed.htm">Nuclear Medicine</a></td></tr>  
	<tr><td><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td>    
                                         <td><a href="angio.htm">Interventional Radiology</a></td></tr>  
               <tr><td><img align=bottom src="blueball.gif"></td>    
                                         <td><a href="bedside.htm">Bedside X-ray</a></td></tr>  
</table></center>
<center><table width="85%"><tr><td>
Professionally our radiologists have sub specialty areas of expertise in all clinical areas, as well as modality specific expertise and training.<br><br>

We have on site radiologists in three satellites, and provide ultrasound services at one remote site via an<a href="ultnet.htm"> ultrsound network</a>.  Virginia Masons satellite program has an emphasis on complete care given in the patients geographic locale. Radiology is a key supporting service to these activities. 
 
</td></tr>  
</table></center>
<CENTER><h3><a href="resmain.htm">Residency Program</a></h3></CENTER>
<center><table width="85%"><tr><td>
I want to take a moment to comment on the unique educational opportunities offered by our residency program.  Our satellite system provides the program with  a large primary care base. Because we are a regional referral, or tertiary care center, we have the opportunity to care for large numbers of patients with extremely complex medical problems.  Virginia Mason is a multispecialty clinic that prides itself on the very close working relationships developed between its clinical colleagues. We have the opportunity to learn from them, while at the same time provide better patient care.<br><br>  

The residency training program is small, with a high faculty to resident ratio that allows residents and staff to have a close working relationship.  Interesting clinical material is discussed formally or informally by residents and staff.  There are no fellows in our program, so residents have access to all patient volume and are one on one with staff.  Our residents do extremely well on national board examinations, and more importantly in obtaining fellowships and jobs once residency training is complete.  Our curriculum has a unique feature of an additional focus on the business side of radiology and the implications of our nations changing health care environment on diagnostic imaging.<br><br>

Again, I extend a personal welcome to our Internet pages.  We sincerely appreciate your interest.<br><br>

Sincerely,<br><br>

Michael S. Morishima, M.D.<br>
Chief, Department of Radiology<br>
<a href="mailto:radmsm@vmmc.org">radmsm@vmmc.org</a>
</td></tr>  
</table></center>
