<center><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="vmbbarw.gif"></center>
<CENTER><H1><B>Lower Extremity</B></H1></CENTER>

<center><table CELLSPACING=1 CELLPADDING=1 width="85%">
             <tr><td width=35%><IMG ALIGN=bottom SRC="lowext.gif"></td>
             <td width=65%><font size=-1>The Lower Extremity consists of the, Hip, Femer {thigh), Knee, Tibia and Fibula (lower leg) ankle and foot.<br><br></font>
<b><i>Preparation</i></b><br>
<font size=-1>There is no preparation for the patient in order to examine the lower extremity other than to remove hardware such as splints or ace bandages.  If a cast is applied to the injured part, films are taken with the cast on.<br><br></font>
<b><i>Procedure</i></b><br>
<font size=-1>Generally examinations of the lower extremity are done with the patient lying or sitting on the x-ray table.  At times, images from the lower extemity will be taken while the patient is still on the stretcher.  <br><br>
.</font>
</td></tr></table></center>


