<HEAD>
   <TITLE>VMRC - ACRU Prior Studies</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; U) [Netscape]">
   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Ron Klapperich">
   <META NAME="KeyWords" CONTENT="research, arthritis, schleraderma, clinic, drug, trial, pharmaceutical, pharmacology, pharmacokinetic, disease, pathogen, therapy, rheumatic, rheumatoid, FDA">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000EE" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#FF0000" BACKGROUND="http://www.vmmc.org/vmrc/acru/vmbg.gif">

<TABLE CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH="80%" >
<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="vmsqlog2.jpg" ALT="VMMC logo" HSPACE=15 HEIGHT=101 WIDTH=100 ALIGN=CENTER></TD>

<TD align="left" nowrap><FONT SIZE=+2>Arthritis Clinical Research Unit<BR>
Virginia Mason Research Center<BR>
Dr. Daniel Furst</FONT></TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="hr.gif" HEIGHT=4 WIDTH=400></P></CENTER>

<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Some of the studies we have completed:</H3>

<CENTER><TABLE WIDTH="80%" >
<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>A double-blind, randomized, multi-center study of multi-drug combination
regimens versus methotrexate plus prednisone in rheumatoid arthritis.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>A double-blind, randomized, multi-center study comparing the onset
of action of three doses of hydroxychloroquine in early rheumatoid arthritis.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>Pharmacokinetics of hydroxychloroquine, its metabolites and enantiomers
in rheumatoid arthr1tis.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>Examination of the pharmacokinetics/pharmacodynamic interface in patients
with rheumatoid arthritis treated with hydroxychloroquine.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>Double-blind, dose-ranging study of a primatized anti-CD4 monoclonal
antibody in rheumatoid arthritis.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>Double-blind, placebo controlled trial of DHEA in mild systemic lupus
erythematosus.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>Double-blind placebo controlled trial of an oral prostacylin derivative
in Raynaud's phenomenon associated with scleroderma.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>Double-blind placebo controlled trial of oral pilocarpine for Sjogren's
Syndrome.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>Long-term, open-label extension examining the safety of chicken collagen
II in the treatment of rheumatoid arthritis.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>A double-blind, randomized, parallel, placebo-controlled, multi-center
comparison of three dosing regimens of sTNFR-IgG in patients with rheumatoid
arthritis.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>Long-term, open-label, extension study examining the tolerability of
sTNFR-IgG in patients with rheumatoid arthritis.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>A double-blind, randomized, two-year study of low vs. high-dose D-penicillamine
in early diffuse systemlc sclerosls.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>A double-blind, placebo-controlled, study examining the usefulness
of methotrexate vs. placebo in the treatment of the skin and of internal
organ involvement in patients with early diffuse systemic sclerosis.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>Cyclophosphamide vs. d-penicillamine in the treatment of systemic sclerosis:
a double-blind, randomized, study of systemic sclerosis patients with early
pulmonary mvolvement.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>
<UL>
<LI>Double-blind placebo controlled trial of a cyclo-oxygenase II inhibitor
in rheumatoid arthritis.</LI>
</UL>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="hr.gif" HEIGHT=4 WIDTH=400></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><TABLE WIDTH="80%" >
<TR>
<TD><A HREF="http://www.vmmc.org/vmrc/ArthritisResearch.html">Arthritis
Clinical Research Unit<BR>
</A><A HREF="http://www.vmmc.org/vmrc/vmrc.html">VMRC Home</A> </TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>

</BODY>
</HTML>
