Last-modified: Wed, 05 Feb 1997 02:22:06 GMT
</DOCHDR>
<!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN">
<HTML>
<HEAD>
   <TITLE>VMRC - PROSORBA COLUMN TREATMENT FOR RHEUMATOID ARTHRITIS</TITLE>
   <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Mozilla/3.0Gold (Win95; U) [Netscape]">
   <META NAME="Author" CONTENT="Ron Klapperich">
   <META NAME="KeyWords" CONTENT="research, arthritis, schleraderma, clinic, drug, trial, pharmaceutical, pharmacology, pharmacokinetic, disease, pathogen, therapy, rheumatic, rheumatoid, FDA">
</HEAD>
<BODY TEXT="#000000" BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF" LINK="#0000EE" VLINK="#551A8B" ALINK="#FF0000" BACKGROUND="vmbg.gif">

<TABLE CELLSPACING=0 CELLPADDING=0 WIDTH="80%" >
<TR>
<TD><IMG SRC="vmsqlog2.jpg" ALT="VMMC logo" HSPACE=15 HEIGHT=101 WIDTH=100 ALIGN=CENTER></TD>

<TD align="left" nowrap>
<H3><FONT SIZE=+2>Arthritis Clinical Research Unit<BR>
Virginia Mason Research Center<BR>
Dr. Daniel Furst</FONT></H3>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>

<H4 ALIGN=CENTER>PROSORBA COLUMN TREATMENT FOR RHEUMATOID ARTHRITIS</H4>

<CENTER><TABLE WIDTH="80%" >
<TR>
<TD>If you have any questions about the Prosorba study, call (206) 223-6836
and press 5 to contact the study coordinator, Donna Ruttkay. If you would
like to participate in the study, call Donna and she will ask you eligibility
questions based on the following study criteria. 
<H3 ALIGN=CENTER><IMG SRC="hr.gif" HEIGHT=4 WIDTH=400> </H3>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>

<CENTER><TABLE WIDTH="80%" >
<TR VALIGN=TOP>
<TD>Objective: </TD>

<TD VALIGN=TOP>
<DT>To evaluate the safety and effectiveness of Prosorba (c) column therapy
in the treatment of patients with rheumatoid arthritis.</DT>
</TD>
</TR>

<TR VALIGN=TOP>
<TD>Design:</TD>

<TD>28 weeks, double-blind, sham-controlled study. Open-label extension
available after 20 weeks on study.</TD>
</TR>

<TR ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP>
<TD>Inclusions: </TD>

<TD ALIGN=LEFT VALIGN=TOP HEIGHT="100%">1. <I>Age 18 or older</I> <BR>
2. <I>RA by ACR criteria</I> <BR>
3. &gt;19 tender joints; &gt;9 swollen joints <BR>
4. NSAID-OK; prednisone &lt;11 mg per day <BR>
5. <I>Good venous access<BR>
</I>6. <I>Failed &gt;1 DMARD</I> <BR>
7. If on DMARD, 30 day or longer washout</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP>Exclusions: </TD>

<TD>1. Hct &lt; 27, Hgb &lt; 9.0 <BR>
2. Other forms of arthritis except osteoarthritis. <BR>
3. Cyclosporin A, cyclophosphamide, or monoclonal antibodies within 90
days. <BR>
4. Active malignancy, except non-metastaic skin cancer. <BR>
5. Infection. <BR>
6. Anti-coagulant. <BR>
7. Active peptic ulcer or inflammatory bowel disease. <BR>
8. Sensitivity to staphylococcal products. <BR>
9. Usual other disease exclusions, pregnancy, etc.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP>Procedures:</TD>

<TD>History, physical examination, arthritis evaluation, blood and urine
tests, HAQ questionnaires at 3 baseline visits; blood and urine tests,
arthritis evaluation, and HAQ at week 6, 12, 16, 20 24, &amp; 28.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP>Treatment: </TD>

<TD>2/3 of patients on column; 1/3 on sham. After 3 baseline visits for
safety and qualifiation, 12 weekly visits for pharesis (requires venous
access) followed by monthly follow-up for 4 months (Total time: 28 weeks
- total visits: 19). Each treatment visit: about 3 hours; each evaluation
visit about 1 hr. If needed portacath insertion can be considered.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP>Toxicity: </TD>

<TD>Local site inflammation (where needle inserted). Arthritis flare 4
to 72 hours after treatment (will treat with analgesia as needed so flare
is not too bad). Fatigue/tiredness, tingling/numbness, nausea/vomiting,
pain, chills/rigors, minor fever, HA, hypotension, diarrhea, lightheadedness/faintness,
gassiness, trouble sleeping, feeling cold, stomach bloating. Dilutional
decrease in hematocrit and/or creatinine.</TD>
</TR>

<TR>
<TD>Reimbursement: </TD>

<TD>Treatments and visits, lab tests, etc. free--plus $15 per visit.</TD>
</TR>

<TR VALIGN=TOP>
<TD>Open Study:</TD>

<TD>Available for patients completing protocol (baseline, all treatments
plus at least 2-months follow-up --20 weeks).</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>

<CENTER><P><IMG SRC="hr.gif" HEIGHT=4 WIDTH=400></P></CENTER>

<CENTER><TABLE WIDTH="80%" >
<TR>
<TD><A HREF="http://www.vmmc.org/vmrc/ArthritisResearch.html">Arthritis
Clinical Research Unit<BR>
</A><A HREF="http://www.vmmc.org/vmrc/vmrc.html">VMRC Home</A> </TD>
</TR>
</TABLE></CENTER>

</BODY>
</HTML>
