<H4>08/19/96</H4>
<UL>
<LI>WASHINGTON (ENN) - The <A href=http://www.usdoj.gov/>U.S. Justice Department</A> World Wide Web site was trashed by computer hackers on Saturday.  The hackers
embedded swastikas, obscene pictures and criticism of the
Communications Decency Act on the web site.  When the infiltration
was discovered, Justice Department computer operators shut down
the home page.</b>.

</UL>


<H4>08/18/96</H4>
<UL>
<LI>The Net has recently experienced a series of Denial of Service attacks by hackers who found disagreements with each other at DefCon, in July of 1996. This <a href="../hacker/cc3.html-ssi">open letter</a> was published a day or so ago, and contains some rough language. If you want to understand one mentality of the Internet, this is a must-read, but please do be forwarned of the <b>unexpurgated phrases and offensive opinions</b>.
</UL>


<UL>
<LI><a href="../civil_de/Cyberwar.html-ssi">Clinton's Cyberwar Executive Order</A> regarding the Establishment of  President's Commission on Critical Infrastructure Protection.

</UL>


