<td width=440>



<Center><B>Here is How and Why you might want<BR> to reach any of us here at Infowar.Com.<BR>
</B></center>

<H4>Sponsorships</H4>
Be Linked and Be Seen on the Premier Infowar and Infosec site. <a href="ads1.html-ssi">Sponsorship Information without the hard sell.</a>


<H4>Submissions</H4>
We are actively looking for your thinking in the areas of Information Warfare and 
Information Security. Give us your tired work or your finished work for the world to see.
<UL>
<LI>Technology
<LI>Privacy
<LI>Policy
<LI>Espionage
<LI>Military
<LI>InfoSec
<LI>Opinion
<LI>Terrorism
<LI>Reviews
<LI>Redigested/Digested 
<LI>Whatever . . .</UL>

You may submit new works (please so identify), previously published works 
(please identify the original source and make sure you have the rights to post 
them). Please insure copyrights are proper, trademarks are in place (recognition 
is good!) and include a way you can be reached electronically and/or hard copy.

<P>Please let us know where you think your submission is best put. We'll listen and 
maybe even do what you ask; no guarantees, though. Our esteemed staff has a 
mind of its own and will do what they think is best.</P>

<P>We prefer submissions attached in a decent format, like Word 'cause they're 
easier to massage. If you really, really have no other choice, then TXT is OK, but 
it goes to the bottom of the list due to time constraints. Sorry.

<a href="MAILTO:webwarrior@infowar.com">Submit@Infowar.Com</A></P>

<H4>News and What's New</H4>

<P>We want to know what's new, hot and of interest to our audience and we'll count 
on you to help out. We'll do what we can - but there are limits. (Interactivity 
defined . . .) </P>
<UL>
<LI>	News
	<IL>Events of note
<LI>	Press Releases, 
<LI>	Product Announcements, 
<LI>	Whatever. 
</UL>
<BR>
<P>Fine by us. We may abbreviate the lenghtier wordy ones, but that's up to us. 
OK? </P>

<P>We'll stay on top of this daily if not faster.</P>

<P>Or call us at <a href="MAILTO:webwarrior@infowar.com">News@Infowar.Com</A> for, guess what . . .News and items of interest to everyone. Not to be shy. </P>

<H4>Comments</H4>

<p>Tell us what you think? Please do. </P>

<P>Isn't this site amazing? (Well, it will be, with your help.) What can we do to make 
it better and more suit your needs? Please be honest, not too brutal, and 
constructive. :-)  
<a href="MAILTO:webwarrior@infowar.com">WebWarrior@Infowar.Com</A></P>

<H4>Who's Who </H4>

<P>If you'd like to be listed in the Who's Who of Information Warfare or Information 
Security, please send us the basics. If your resume/accomplishments are too 
long, we reserve the right to edit your ego down to size. <G> Seriously; just the 
basics, a short description and a hyperlink back to your page will do just fine.</P>

<p>Also, let us know about <B>resources</B> that should be added to our lists and about 
participatory <B>events</B> or happenings (trade shows, conferences, Senate hearings, 
etc.) around the world that everyone should know about.</P>

Mail us whatever you have. <A HREF="MAILTO:webwarrior@infowar.com">Who's Who,  Resources, and Events</A>

