<H4>List Servers</H4> 
 
<P>
In the next few weeks, Infowar.Com lists will begin fullfilling all of our on-line discussion needs in the following areas. </P> 
<UL> 
<LI>Infowar - The Big Picture<BR>
<!--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------->
<DL><DT>
<DT><FORM ACTION="http://www.infowar.com/cgi-shl/discuss.pl" METHOD="post">
<Input type="hidden" Name="list" value="infowar"></DT>
	<DD><INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="join_type" VALUE="digest" CHECKED>Digested list -- 1 Digested group of messages per day</DD>
	<DD><INPUT TYPE="radio" NAME="join_type" VALUE="join">Undigested list -- each post is forwarded separately</DD>
    	<DD>E-Mail Address: <INPUT NAME="email" SIZE=30> <INPUT TYPE="submit" VALUE="  Join  "></DD>
</FORM>
	<DD> 
This is the first list that will begin. Shortly, and based upon interest, we will commence with the following
discussion groups. Note:  To change delivery format, rejoin your selected list with the same E-mail address with the selected option. 
</DD>
</DL>
<!---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------> 
<BR> 
 
<LI>Terrorism, To be Moderated by Matt DeVost<BR> 
 
<BR> 
<LI>Hackers, To be Moderated by Chris Goggans<BR> 
 
<BR> 
<LI>OSINT - Open Source Intelligence, To be Moderated by Robert Steele<BR> 
 
<BR> 
<LI>Internet Security/Firewalls <BR> 
 
<BR> 
 
</UL>
 
But it doesn't end there. We will add more of what <B>you want</B>. More lists to focus on those areas and topics that make sense to Information Warriors and Information Security Professionals everywhere. 
 
If when you registered for Infowar.Com, you chose to be on our mailing list, you will be automatically notified how to subscribe to each group. We will maintain on line archives of the raw feeds to the lists as well as the digested version. Both will be available for searches. 
 
If you have ideas on future list servers, please <a href="MAILTO:webwarrior@infowar.com">let us know</A>. 
<BR> 
 
<h4>Bulletin Boards</H4> 
 
Infowar.Com will also open internal real-time discussion groups in use-net fashion, sometime later this year. If you'd like to assist or have any ideas, please do let us know. 
<BR> 
<h4>Conferencing</h4> 
 
Not today, not next week, but soon, Infowar.Com will install complete audio and video conferencing facilities so Info-warriors world wide can communicate in human ways at no more cost than sending email. Once we all get the hang of it, we hope to use it for broadcast of events as they occur. 
<BR> 
