<h4>Policy</H4>


<BR>


<H4>Terrorism</H4>
  
 <LI>Robert Steele's excellent suggestions on <a href="class3_o.html-ssi">RIGHTSIZING INTELLIGENCE RESOURCES.</a> Bottom line..." U.S. intelligence community cannot get healthy without making a modest but significant investment in open sources, while also reducing its secret baggage by one third."<BR>
<BR>
 <LI><img border=0 src="coolhot.gif"> More on the FLT 800 Missile Thoery - <a href="class3_n.html-ssi">A rebuttal</a><BR>
<BR>
<LI><a href="class3_m.html-ssi">Top German prosecutor</a> warns firms about espionage.<BR>
<BR>
 <LI><img border=0 src="coolhot.gif"><a href="class3_l.html-ssi">From ENN Special Report</a> - A further look at TWA FL800 and the recent press coverage  by former TV correspondent Pierre Salinger.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><a href="class3_k.html-ssi">WEAPONS OF MASS DESTRUCTION IN TERRORISM</a>   The Emerging Threat Posed by Non-State Proliferation.  Cmdr. Campbell
states,..." To date most informed opinions on non-state political violence
suggest that terrorist of the future will neither seek to develop, nor
threaten to use weapons of mass destruction (WMD)."  Exellent reading.<BR>
<BR>
<LI>A good read by Ralph McGehee on <a href="class3_j.html-ssi">"CIA's Failure of Intelligence
RE: Terrorism".</a><BR>
<BR>
<LI> From Sweden, <a href="class3_i.html-ssi">DESTA Newsletter.</a><BR>
<BR>
<LI>From Steve Macko at ENN, <a href="class3_h.html-ssi">HOW THE CIA COMBATS INTERNATIONAL
TERRORISM.</a><BR>
<BR>
<LI><a href="class3_g.html-ssi">HUMINT STILL MOST IMPORTANT</a> WHEN THWARTING TERRORISTS<BR>
<BR> 
<LI>Deputy Attorney General speaks on <a href="class3_f.html-ssi">computer terrorism<BR>
<BR> 

<LI>Perry announces <a href="class3_d.html-ssi">DOD to drop torture from training</a><BR>
<BR>
<LI>From ENN:  <a href="class3_e.html-ssi">DOD's Anti-Terrorism Conference</a> Ft. Walton Beach, FL<BR>
<BR>
<LI><a href="class3_c.html-ssi"> "Cybergangs"</a> On the Internet<BR>
<BR> 
<LI>Michael Wilson's,  <a href="class3_b.html-ssi">"Terrorism in a New World--THE EVOLUTION IN
REVOLUTION"</a> - a great read.  The title says it all.<BR>
<BR>
<LI>By John Dermaut, <a href="class3_7.html-ssi">DISTURBING "DEJA ENTENDU"AND "DEJA VU".</a> This article was written assuming that the TWA 800 plane was downed by an explosive device.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><a href="class3_6.html-ssi">Denial of Service</a> Hits NY ISP.<BR>
