<H4>Hacker Cons</H4>
<UL>
   <LI><a href="hackd.html-ssi">Hackers Hack Sky-TV</a><BR>
<BR>
   <LI>UK: CONNECTED - <a href="hackc.html-ssi"> - SECURITY HACKING USED TO BE ALMOST RESPECTABLE.</a><BR>
<BR>
   <LI>EDITORIAL - <a href="hackb.html-ssi">HACKER VS. CRACKER</a><BR>
<BR>
   <LI>Latest Hacker Convention:  <a href="hacka.html-ssi">CUERVOCON 96</a><BR>
<BR>
      <LI><a href="hack9.html-ssi">Major Internet Server Platform Vulnerable to Hacker Attacks</a><BR>
<BR>
      <LI>From ENN, <a href="hack8.html-ssi">WWW page owned to British Labour Party, hacked.</a><BR>
<BR>
     <LI><a href="hack7.html-ssi">"The Happy Hacker"</a> A New addition to Infowar.Com. The Happy Hacker is a sort of flame-war instigator and retardant, all in one. Lots to learn here. Let 
us know what you think.<BR>
<BR>
 <LI><a href="hack6.html-ssi">Totem & Taboo in Cyberspace</a> by M. E. Kabay, Ph.D., Director of Education, NCSA. This insightful piece ponders behavior and morals in 
Cyberspace. Hackers have responded less than pleasantly to this article.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><a href="hack5.html-ssi">SPA vs. Site with Hack links?</a> Private Big Brother?<BR>
<BR> 

<LI><img border=0 src="../class_1/coolhot.gif"> Hackers crack <a href="hack4.html-ssi">CIA home page code.</a><BR>
<BR>
 <LI> Hacker Alert!  Don't miss this! <a href="hack3.html-ssi">OSS'96</a><BR>
<BR>
 <LI><a href="cc1short.html-ssi">Cyber Christ Meets Lady Luck</a> This raunchy but realistic account of what really happens at a hacker conference has been banned in some places on the Net. <B>Be warned!</B> Some people could be offended by the Hunter Thompson style. Written by Winn Schwartau.<BR>
<BR>
<LI><a href="cc2short.html-ssi">Cyber Christ Bites The Big Apple</a> is a fun-filled report on activities at Hackers on Planet Earth Conference, NYC.<BR>
<BR> 
<!--<LI>Nic Chantler from Australia, and a former intelligence officer, wrote his <a href="chap1fin.html-ssi">Doctoral Thesis</a> on computer hackers. This is Part I, 46K,  of a long ZIP file available for download. Great material and research.<BR>
<BR>-->

<LI>Quotes on the Department of Justice <a href="hack2.html-ssi">Web Site Hack.</a><BR>
<BR>
<LI>For a totally inreverant look at Computer Crime, Infowar and an assorted batch of related insanities, grab a beer, put on Hooty and the Blowfish and <a href="http://www.digicrime.com">click away.</a><BR>
<BR>
</UL>

<h4>Comments and Review</H4>
<UL>
<LI><a href="takedow1.html-ssi">A critically funny review of 'Takedown' </a> the Shimomuro tale by himself and John Markoff, by Winn Schwartau. <BR>
<BR>
<LI><a href="crimhack.html-ssi">Why Criminal Hackers Must Not Be Rewarded</a> by 
Mich E.  Kabay, Ph.D., Director of Education, National Computer Security Association.<BR>
<BR>
<LI>Ira Winkler wrote <a href="whohacks.html-ssi">Who Are The Hackers?</a> and is worth  your time whether you agree or not.<BR>
<BR>
</UL>

<h4>Hackers Themselves</H4>

<UL>
<LI>The Net has recently experienced a series of Denial of Service attacks by hackers who found disagreements with each other at DefCon, in July of 1996. This <a href="cc3.html-ssi">open letter</a> was published a day or so ago, and contains some rough language. If you want to understand one mentality of the Internet, this is a must-read, but please do be forwarned of the unexpurgated phrases and offensive opinions.<BR>
<BR>

</UL>

<UL>
<LI>Transcripts of <a href="se_1.html-ssi">Real Live Social Engineering</a> by hackers performing at their best. Fascinating and educational. A must-read for security training and awareness.<BR>
<BR>

</UL>

<UL>
<LI>US Soldier Accused of: <a href="hack1.html-ssi">"Cracking"</a> for foreign power.
<BR>

</UL>

